<div class="mathjax-guide-container modal fade" id="mathjax-guide">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h3> MathJax Guide </h3>
      </div>

      <div class="modal-body">
        To include math in question text or answer choices, surround
        mathematical expressions with
        <ul>
          <li><pre>\[ ... \]</pre> for block math, or</li>
          <li><pre>\( ... \)</pre> for inline math</li>
        </ul>
        and use
        <ul>
          <li><pre>\frac{...}{...}</pre> for fractions</li>
          <li><pre>\sqrt{...}</pre> for square root</li>
          <li><pre>^</pre> for superscripts</li>
          <li><pre>_</pre> for superscripts</li>
        </ul>
        <div>
          <strong>Examples</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <pre>\( f_1(x) = x^\frac{1}{3} = \sqrt[3]{x} \)</pre>
              produces
              \( f_1(x) = x^\frac{1}{3} = \sqrt[3]{x}  \)
            </li>

            <li>
              The following:<br>
              <pre>
\[
    \begin{align}
      f_1'(x)
      &= \frac{1}{3} x^{-\frac{2}{3}} \\
      &= \frac{1}{3} \sqrt[3]{x^2}
    \end{align}
\]
              </pre><br>
              produces:
              \[
                  \begin{align}
                  f_1'(x)
                  &= \frac{1}{3} x^{-\frac{2}{3}} \\
                  &= \frac{1}{3} \sqrt[3]{x^2}
                  \end{align}
              \]
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        See this
        <a
          href="https://math.meta.stackexchange.com/questions/5020/mathjax-basic-tutorial-and-quick-reference"
          target="_blank"
        >MathJax tutorial</a> for more.
      </div>

      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button
          type="button"
          class="btn btn-secondary"
          data-dismiss="modal">
          Close
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
